terest%20and%20earnings%20from%20savings%20accounts%2C%20CDs%2C%20and%20other%20investments%20are%20considered%20taxable%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%2C%20I%20didn't%20realize%20that%2C%20and%20I%20spent%20a%20lot%20of%20this%20passive%20income%20on%20vacations%2C%20building%20my%20business%2C%20and%20paying%20off%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-credit-cards%5C%22%3Ecredit%20cards%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20after%20getting%20hit%20with%20a%20big%20tax%20bill%20in%202023%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20be%20more%20strategic%20about%20the%20tax%20implications%20that%20come%20from%20moving%20money%20between%20accounts%20to%20optimize%20interest.%20Here's%20how%20I%20planned%20for%20my%202023%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Ftaxes%5C%22%3Etax%20bill%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E1.%20I%20don't%20spend%20the%20interest%20as%20soon%20as%20I%20get%20it%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20my%20accountant%20shared%20how%20much%20I%20owed%20in%20taxes%20for%202022%2C%20I%20was%20sure%20she%20had%20made%20a%20mistake.%20But%20she%20mentioned%20that%20a%20reason%20my%20bill%20was%20so%20high%20was%20because%20I%20earned%20a%20lot%20in%20interest%20from%20my%20high-yield%20savings%20account%20and%20didn't%20pay%20any%20taxes%20on%20that%20income%20throughout%20the%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20most%20of%20that%20money%20was%20spent%20or%20reinvested%20into%20my%20business%2C%20I%20decided%20that%20I%20wouldn't%20touch%20that%20money%20until%20after%20tax%20season%20ended.%20That%20helped%20me%20reframe%20my%20finances.%20Instead%20of%20thinking%20I%20have%20a%20few%20thousand%20dollars%20to%20spend%20throughout%20the%20year%2C%20I%20don't%20account%20for%20those%20earnings%20as%20part%20of%20my%20overall%20net%20worth.%20Instead%2C%20after%20paying%20my%20taxes%2C%20I%20reassess%20how%20much%20money%20of%20interest%20income%20I%20actually%20made%20and%20decide%20how%20to%20use%20the%20cash%20then.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20I%20use%20the%20interest%20to%20pay%20my%20taxes%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20solopreneur%2C%20I%20pay%20both%20corporate%20and%20personal%20taxes%20every%20year.%20While%20my%20accountant%20and%20I%20do%20a%20good%20job%20of%20withholding%20money%20from%20each%20of%20my%20paychecks%20for%20taxes%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fhow-to-pay-quarterly-taxes%5C%22%3Epaying%20quarterly%20taxes%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20estimated%20tax%20payments%2C%20I%20still%20have%20a%20tax%20bill%20that's%20a%20few%20thousand%20dollars%2C%20or%20more%2C%20every%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20I%20don't%20like%20to%20tap%20into%20my%20personal%20savings%20to%20pay%20off%20this%20tax%20bill%2C%20I%20often%20consider%20the%20interest%20and%20earnings%20I'm%20making%20from%20my%20money%20movement%20strategy%20and%20passive%20income%20investments%20as%20means%20to%20cover%20my%20tax%20bill.%20I%20now%20wait%20to%20spend%20that%20money%20until%20after%20I%20know%20how%20much%20I%20owe%20in%20taxes%20and%20often%20use%20at%20least%20half%20of%20that%20money%20to%20cover%20the%20full%20bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E3.%20I%20buy%20some%20SEP%20IRA%20CDs%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EKeeping%20cash%20in%20high-interest-earning%20CDs%20is%20a%20major%20part%20of%20my%20money%20strategy.%20When%20I%20have%20extra%20money%20coming%20in%20from%20a%20good%20month%20of%20work%20or%20one%20of%20my%20high-yield%20savings%20accounts%20drops%20the%20interest%20rate%2C%20I'll%20put%20that%20money%20in%20various%20types%20of%20CDs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20CD%20that%20has%20tax%20benefits%20is%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-ira-cd%5C%22%3ESEP%20IRA%20CD%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20considered%20a%20retirement%20investment%20account.%20Any%20interest%20gained%20from%20money%20in%20this%20CD%20remains%20tax%20deferred%20until%20distributions%20are%20made%20at%20retirement.%20However%2C%20unlike%20a%20regular%20CD%2C%20CDs%20in%20your%20retirement%20fund%20have%20contribution%20limits%20set%20by%20the%20IRS.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E4.%20I'm%20strategic%20with%20short-term%20CDs%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20solopreneur%2C%20my%20income%20varies%20quite%20a%20lot%20throughout%20the%20year.%20Around%20November%2C%20I'll%20chat%20with%20my%20accountant%2C%20and%20if%20I'm%20having%20a%20higher%20income%20year%20than%20usual%2C%20I'll%20plan%20for%20that%20to%20lower%20my%20overall%20tax%20bill.%20One%20strategy%20I%20have%20used%20in%20the%20past%20is%20to%20buy%20a%20short-term%20CD%20that%20doesn't%20come%20due%20until%20January%20or%20February%20of%20the%20next%20year.%20This%20helps%20defer%20taxes%20on%20that%20money%20until%20the%20next%20year%20when%20taxable%20income%20might%20be%20lower.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsmartasset.com%2Fretirement%2Ffind-a-financial-planner%3Futm_source%3Dbusinessinsider%26utm_medium%3Dcpc%26utm_campaign%3Dbus__falc_bicontent%26utm_content%3DBI%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFinding%20a%20financial%20advisor%3C%2Fa%3E%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be%20hard.%20SmartAsset's%20free%20tool%20matches%20you%20with%20up%20to%20three%20fiduciary%20financial%20advisors%20that%20serve%20your%20area%20in%20minutes.%20Each%20advisor%20has%20been%20vetted%20by%20SmartAsset%20and%20is%20held%20to%20a%20fiduciary%20standard%20to%20act%20in%20your%20best%20interests.%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsmartasset.com%2Fretirement%2Ffind-a-financial-planner%3Futm_source%3Dbusinessinsider%26utm_medium%3Dcpc%26utm_campaign%3Dbus__falc_bicontent%26utm_content%3DBI%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Start%20your%20search%20now.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fplan-for-tax-season-savings-strategy-2024-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%2