0my%20husband%E2%80%99s%20addiction%20made%20things%20worse.%20He%2C%20in%20a%20state%20of%20intoxication%2C%20either%20sold%20off%20his%20land%20or%20gambled%20it%20away%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELeft%20without%20a%20means%20to%20feed%20her%20family%2C%20Bhimabai%20would%20work%20for%20hours%20in%20different%20people%E2%80%99s%20fields%20to%20bring%20food%20to%20the%20table.%20%E2%80%9CI%20was%20fed%20up%20with%20the%20life%20we%20had.%20My%20son%20was%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F342483%2Fmadhya-pradesh-school-teacher-gopal-bhalwala-renovates-government-school-with-own-savings%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egoing%20to%20school%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20had%20picked%20up%20a%20newspaper%20distribution%20job%20to%20help%20me%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPravin%20elaborates%20on%20his%20mother%E2%80%99s%20struggle%20from%20his%20perspective%2C%20%E2%80%9CAll%20the%20relatives%20were%20always%20trying%20to%20have%20their%20way%20with%20her.%20My%20father%20was%20a%20father%20only%20in%20name.%20He%20never%20took%20any%20responsibilities.%20Like%20my%20mother%2C%20I%20had%20a%20zeal%20to%20get%20an%20education.%20I%20got%20a%20job%20at%20a%20newspaper%20distributor%20and%20funded%20my%20education%20myself%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20only%20one%20escape%20from%20the%20challenging%20life%20%E2%80%93%20move%20to%20the%20city.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20like%20a%20beacon%20of%20hope%20for%20us.%20I%20would%20probably%20find%20some%20work%20there%2C%20and%20my%20mother%20would%20be%20away%20from%20her%20relatives.%20So%2C%20we%20decided%20to%20sell%20off%20whatever%20was%20left%20of%20our%20land%20and%20moved%20to%20the%20city%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202008%2C%20the%20family%20moved%20to%20the%20city.%20Pravin%20had%20already%20started%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%